#converting the key column into seperate column containing date, time , hour etc

train_df['pickup_datetime']  = pd.to_datetime(train_df['pickup_datetime'])
test_df['key'] = pd.to_datetime(test_df['key'])
test_df['pickup_datetime']  = pd.to_datetime(test_df['pickup_datetime'])
data = [train_df,test_df]
for i in data:
    i['Year'] = i['pickup_datetime'].dt.year
    i['Month'] = i['pickup_datetime'].dt.month
    i['Date'] = i['pickup_datetime'].dt.day
    i['Day of Week'] = i['pickup_datetime'].dt.dayofweek
    i['Hour'] = i['pickup_datetime'].dt.hour

In [10]:
#as the latitude and longitute values are processed using this haversine and calculated the distance in km
import math
def haversine(coord1, coord2):
    R = 6371  # Earth radius in meters
    lat1, lon1 = coord1
    lat2, lon2 = coord2
    
    phi1, phi2 = math.radians(lat1), math.radians(lat2) 
    dphi       = math.radians(lat2 - lat1)
    dlambda    = math.radians(lon2 - lon1)
    
    a = math.sin(dphi/2)**2 + \
        math.cos(phi1)*math.cos(phi2)*math.sin(dlambda/2)**2
    
    return 2*R*math.atan2(math.sqrt(a), math.sqrt(1 - a))

#Calculating distance using latitude and longitute
dist_train=[]
dist_test=[]
index_train=train_df.index.tolist()
index_test=test_df.index.tolist()

for i in index_train:
    d=haversine((train_df['pickup_latitude'][i],train_df['pickup_longitude'][i]),(train_df['dropoff_latitude'][i],train_df['dropoff_longitude'][i]))
    dist_train.append(d)

for i in index_test:
    d=haversine((test_df['pickup_latitude'][i],test_df['pickup_longitude'][i]),(test_df['dropoff_latitude'][i],test_df['dropoff_longitude'][i]))
    dist_test.append(d)
